title: For Sale:  Winchester Model 94 25/35 Flatband
postcontent: Winchester Model 94 25/35 Carbine, Its in good working order and condition, obviously its one of the rarest model 94's out there with a production estimation of about 10,000 25/35 flat band rifles made.  Looking at its markings and setup, its probably a 1947 early 1948 production (1442***), however the receiver may have sat in the factory for a while as it has the look of the higher nickel content prewar receiver, which whilst harder and more durable struggled to maintain the original blueing, whilst the barrel, mag tube ect have maintained an almost perfect finish.  Serated hammer, marked 25-35 WCF (earlier marking), very rare tang markings, as in there are none, deleted peep sight screw hole.  Original Ramp sight and hood.  Wood is in good condition, hasnt been broken minor surface crack on forend a few nicks, hasnt been refinished, serrated butt plate. Looks like its had a great life as a hunting rifle and been carried a lot. I also have a small amount of brass and reloads that can come with the rifle if requested.Open to offers, Possible interested in a part trade, I like old guns, its a great addictionNote - Armslist doesnt have 25/35 listed as a calibre, so I selected 30/30 (its not this calibre)
